
[1]vindication

   VINDICA'TION, n. [L. vindico.]

   1. The defense of any thing, or a justification against denial or
   censure, or against objections or accusations; as the vindication of
   opinions or of a creed; the vindication of the Scriptures against the
   objections and cavils of infidels.

   2. The act of supporting by proof or legal process; the proving of any
   thing to be just; as the vindication of a title, claim or right.

   3. Defense by force or otherwise; as the vindication of the rights of
   man; the vindication of our liberties or the rights of conscience.
